cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a framework for training multiple neural networks simultaneously, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The framework involves regularizing the parameters of all models by the tensor trace norm, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions that the sharing strategy is learned in a data-driven way, which suggests the use of neural networks and optimization techniques commonly used in neural engineering (cs.NE).
